Dialogue: 1,0:09:43.73,0:09:47.38,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and then b comes down
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.73,0:09:47.38,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后B就下来了
Dialogue: 1,0:09:47.38,0:09:53.33,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and there we go and then it's solved uh
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.38,0:09:53.33,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}就这样就解决了
Dialogue: 1,0:09:53.33,0:09:57.88,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}so, you know the trick is you have to put A in halfway
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.33,0:09:57.88,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}所以，诀窍是你必须把A放在一半的地方
Dialogue: 1,0:09:57.88,0:10:01.65,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um back to the presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.88,0:10:01.65,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}回到幻灯片
Dialogue: 1,0:10:01.65,0:10:04.34,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}uh so I mean and this isn't a difficult puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.65,0:10:04.34,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}所以我的意思是，这其实并不是一个很难的谜题
Dialogue: 1,0:10:04.34,0:10:07.80,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}this might be a level one or a level two puzzle it's not particularly challenging
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.34,0:10:07.80,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这可能是第1级或第2级的谜题，没有特别的挑战性
Dialogue: 1,0:10:07.80,0:10:13.75,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}but it illustrates the point of the obvious things lead to a non-solution to the puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.80,0:10:13.75,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但它说明了一点，解谜过程中会有一些明显的东西让这个谜题看起来无解
Dialogue: 1,0:10:13.75,0:10:16.88,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and you might even be convinced like well then this puzzle's impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.75,0:10:16.88,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}并且你甚至可能会说服自己这个谜题是不可能的
Dialogue: 1,0:10:16.88,0:10:21.68,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}you can't put a in first you can't put b in first so clearly it's impossible well okay
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.88,0:10:21.68,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}既不能先放A也不能先放B那显然就不可能了
Dialogue: 1,0:10:21.68,0:10:24.18,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}but there was something that you didn't notice
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.68,0:10:24.18,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但其实有些事情你没有注意到
Dialogue: 1,0:10:24.24,0:10:28.47,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}the state of aporia this state of feeling like the puzzle is impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.24,0:10:28.47,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这种Aporia的感觉，这种觉得谜题不可能的感觉
Dialogue: 1,0:10:28.47,0:10:36.53,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}or simultaneously believing both that well I think it's impossible but yet the puzzle is in front of me and a solution has been promised
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.47,0:10:36.53,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}或者说既感觉这个谜题是不可能，但又觉得这个谜题的解一定是能给出的
Dialogue: 1,0:10:36.53,0:10:42.10,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um it creates this uh idea that an interesting trick exists
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:42.10,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这产生了这样一个想法，一个有趣的诀窍是存在的
Dialogue: 1,0:10:42.10,0:10:48.63,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}it sort of promises you that a powerful eureka moment is coming and primes you for the discovery of something really cool
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.10,0:10:48.63,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}它有点在向你预示一个强大的尤里卡时刻即将到来，并让你为发现很酷的东西做准备
Dialogue: 1,0:10:48.63,0:10:55.54,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and that mystery and anticipation is really motivating like there's a big reveal coming and you can now anticipate it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.63,0:10:55.54,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}那种神秘感和期待真的很有激励性，就像有个大的启示即将到来，已经可以预见它了
Dialogue: 1,0:10:55.54,0:11:06.61,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and the sort of state of anticipating a reward or anticipating a eureka moment is it can be more motivating and more dopaminergic than actually getting the reward
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.54,0:11:06.61,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}那种期待奖励或尤里卡时刻的状态，比实际得到奖励更有动力，有更高多巴胺能
Dialogue: 1,0:11:06.61,0:11:11.35,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um and so this state of aporia is highly motivating
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.61,0:11:11.35,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}所以这种Aporia的状态时有高度激励性的
Dialogue: 1,0:11:11.35,0:11:16.60,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and when a player is convinced that they're just on the cusp of a really cool discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.35,0:11:16.60,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而当玩家相信自己正处在即将有一个非常酷的发现的边缘的时候
Dialogue: 1,0:11:16.60,0:11:21.08,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}that could be a time where they're very unlikely to quit and very likely to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.60,0:11:21.08,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这就是他们不太可能放弃的时刻，而且很可能会记住（这个时刻）
Dialogue: 1,0:11:21.08,0:11:26.84,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and uh you know want to share that discovery once they found it and be very excited by it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.08,0:11:26.84,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而一旦他们解出来了，就会想与别分享，并为之兴奋
Dialogue: 1,0:11:26.84,0:11:28.63,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}so aporia is a great trick
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.84,0:11:28.63,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}所以Aporia是一个很好的技巧
Dialogue: 1,0:11:28.63,0:11:33.68,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}I will show you an example this is from a game called Pipe Push Paradise by Corey Martin a few years back
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.63,0:11:33.68,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我给你看个例子，这是几年前由Corey Martin制作的叫《推管天堂》的游戏
Dialogue: 1,0:11:33.68,0:11:36.24,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}this is a puzzle where you sort of have to push these pipes around
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.68,0:11:36.24,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}谜题中你得把这些管道推来推去
Dialogue: 1,0:11:36.24,0:11:40.28,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and in this puzzle in particular on the left here you have this pipe with water flowing out
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.24,0:11:40.28,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}在这个谜题的左边你能看到一个在流水的管道
Dialogue: 1,0:11:40.28,0:11:42.96,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and you have to connect it to the one on the right
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.28,0:11:42.96,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你得把它跟右边那个连起来
Dialogue: 1,0:11:42.96,0:11:46.68,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and you might realize well okay so you just have to make this u shape with these two pieces
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.96,0:11:46.68,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你可能会意识到，好吧，只需要用这两段管道做成这样一个U字形
Dialogue: 1,0:11:46.68,0:11:49.04,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}you can sort of flip and rotate the pieces around
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.68,0:11:49.04,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你可以翻转和旋转这些管道段
Dialogue: 1,0:11:49.04,0:11:53.08,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}the problem is that when you get to this state you can't leave the puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.04,0:11:53.08,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}问题是，当你做成这个状态时，你就不能走出这个谜题了
Dialogue: 1,0:11:53.08,0:11:56.66,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and you have to both connect the pipes up and have a way of exiting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.08,0:11:56.66,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你必须把管道连接起来并且还要有一个出口
Dialogue: 1,0:11:56.66,0:11:59.73,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}in this case the exit is at the bottom but you just can't get down there
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.66,0:11:59.73,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}在这种情况下，出口在底部，但你走不过去
Dialogue: 1,0:11:59.73,0:12:03.19,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and uh you know once you've played with this puzzle a bit you can realize that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.73,0:12:03.19,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}一旦你玩过这个谜题，你就会发现
Dialogue: 1,0:12:03.19,0:12:08.82,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}there's no way to be at the puzzle at the bottom of this puzzle while also having the pipes in this configuration
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.19,0:12:08.82,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}没有办法把管道弄成这种构造的同时人站在下面
Dialogue: 1,0:12:08.82,0:12:13.24,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}there's just no last move that could have created this configuration and leave you at the bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.82,0:12:13.24,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}没有任何移动能做出这样的构造，而让你站在底部
Dialogue: 1,0:12:13.24,0:12:20.34,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}you could never have pushed those pipes up into that configuration because there wouldn't have been a place for you to stand um
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.24,0:12:20.34,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你不可能把这些管道推到这个位置，因为你根本没有地方可以站立
Dialogue: 1,0:12:20.34,0:12:25.20,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and one of the things that you'll observe if you're playing around with this puzzle enough is that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.34,0:12:25.20,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}如果你多玩一玩，你就会发现
Dialogue: 1,0:12:25.20,0:12:31.54,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}you can actually rotate the pipes into a different configuration where they're out in three dimensions
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:31.54,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你可以把管道旋转到另一种构造，让它们在三维空间中突出来
Dialogue: 1,0:12:31.54,0:12:37.36,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}this is a three-dimensional puzzle solving game where the rotations sometimes take things up off of the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.54,0:12:37.36,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这其实是个三维的解谜游戏，旋转是可以让东西离开地面的
Dialogue: 1,0:12:37.36,0:12:44.21,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and this prompts you to find the real solution which is actually to make the archway in the third dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.36,0:12:44.21,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这就促使你找到真正的解法，就是把“拱门”变成三维的
Dialogue: 1,0:12:44.21,0:12:46.64,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}such that you can walk under it and leave the puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.21,0:12:46.64,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这样你就可以从下面走过去，离开这个谜题
Dialogue: 1,0:12:46.64,0:12:49.40,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and this is a very memorable solution
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.64,0:12:49.40,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这是一个非常令人难忘的解法
Dialogue: 1,0:12:49.40,0:12:56.37,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}but the thing that sort of primes you for this surprise is going back to your first attempt at the solution and realizing this ain't gonna work
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.40,0:12:56.37,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但在这个惊喜之前，回到你最初的尝试，你会发现做不到
Dialogue: 1,0:12:56.37,0:13:00.34,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and perhaps even being so puzzled by it that you might leave the puzzle go try something else
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.37,0:13:00.34,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}也许你会感到非常困惑，以至于暂时离开这个谜题去试试别的
Dialogue: 1,0:13:00.34,0:13:04.44,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and then come back once you've realized that well all the other puzzles had solutions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.34,0:13:04.44,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后当你意识到其他的谜题都有解决方法时又回来
Dialogue: 1,0:13:04.44,0:13:07.70,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}this one must have one but what am i not thinking of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.44,0:13:07.70,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}那这个谜题也一定可解，但是我有什么地方是没想到的吗
Dialogue: 1,0:13:07.70,0:13:10.00,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and that final surprise is just so memorable
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.70,0:13:10.00,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而最后的惊喜是如此令人难忘
Dialogue: 1,0:13:10.00,0:13:17.56,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}both because it's an exciting surprise but also because of the fact that you couldn't solve it any other means
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.00,0:13:17.56,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}既是因为它是一个令人兴奋的惊喜，但也是因为你无法用其他任何方式来解决它的这一点事实
Dialogue: 1,0:13:17.56,0:13:22.61,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}now in order to make this work you have to do this which is our 14th lesson
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:22.61,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}那么，为了让它发挥作用，你必须要做的事正是我们接下来的第14课
Dialogue: 1,0:13:22.61,0:13:26.20,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}cultivate the trust of the solver
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.61,0:13:26.20,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}「建立与解谜者之间的信任」
Dialogue: 1,0:13:26.20,0:13:34.39,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and one example of where this comes up is say you're on the puzzle subreddit or the puzzling stack exchange and you just click on a random interesting puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.20,0:13:34.39,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}有一个例子可以说明这一点，比如你跑到贴吧上或其他网站上随便找了个看起很有趣的谜题
Dialogue: 1,0:13:34.39,0:13:38.29,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and it looks cool but you play around with it a bit and it looks impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.39,0:13:38.29,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}它看起来很酷，但你尝试了一会儿，发现这个看起来解不出来
Dialogue: 1,0:13:38.29,0:13:43.16,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and maybe you've even convinced yourself that it must be impossible you have a proof that it's impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.29,0:13:43.16,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}也许你甚至说服了自己这肯定不可能，你有证据说明它不可能
Dialogue: 1,0:13:43.16,0:13:49.24,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}maybe there's a really cool eureka moment lurking beneath the surface that you just didn't discover yet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.16,0:13:49.24,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}也许有一个非常酷的尤里卡时刻埋藏在表面之下，只是你还没有发现
